headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 26 points, 16 rebounds, seven assists and three blocks in his Mavericks debut but left the game late in the third quarter with a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis leads Mavericks past Rockets 116-105 in Mavs debut but leaves with lower-body injury

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves scored a career-high 45 points and the streaking Los Angeles Lakers beat the Indiana Pacers 124-117 on Saturday without LeBron James or Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Austin Reaves scores a career-high 45, and the Lakers shock the Pacers 124-117 without LeBron, Luka

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero’s 15-foot shot put Orlando ahead with 24.7 seconds left in a game they played mostly from behind and Victor Wembanyama missed a mid-range jumper in the final seconds as the Magic held on for a 112-111 win over the San Antonio Spurs on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero makes a late go-ahead shot and Magic hold off Spurs 112-111

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 35 points and had 14 assists to help the Atlanta Hawks to a 125-111 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 35 points and has 14 assists in Atlanta's 125-111 victory over Washington

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 34 points and tied a season high with eight 3-pointers, Jimmy Butler added 25 points in his Golden State debut and the Warriors rallied to beat the Chicago Bulls 132-111 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 34 points, Butler adds 25 in Golden State debut as Warriors rally to beat Bulls 132-111

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 32 points and Aaron Wiggins added 26 points and 11 rebounds as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Memphis Grizzlies 125-112 on Saturday night in a showdown of the top two teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 32 to lead Thunder past Grizzlies 125-112

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Jaden McDaniels had 30 points, 10 rebounds and four assists, Naz Reid scored 11 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter and the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves overcame a 15-point deficit to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 114-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDaniels, Reid lead Edwards-less Timberwolves past Trail Blazers, 114-98

events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 40 points and the Boston Celtics easily handled the New York Knicks for the second time this season, winning 131-104 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 40 points as the Celtics easily beat the Knicks for the 2nd time this season, 131-104

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists to just miss a triple-double before sitting out the fourth quarter and the Denver Nuggets won their season-best sixth straight game, beating the Phoenix Suns 122-105 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic falls assist short of triple-double in his 3 quarters in Nuggets' 122-105 victory over Suns

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 27 points and 16 rebounds for his NBA-leading 46th double-double of the season and the Sacramento Kings overcame a 20-point deficit for a 123-118 victory over New Orleans on Saturday night that extended the Pelicans’ losing...
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis had 27 and Kings rally from 20 down to beat Pelicans 123-118

headlines.description: — Norman Powell and Ivica Zubac scored 26 points apiece, James Harden added 23 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Utah Jazz 130-110 Saturday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell, Zubac both score 26 as Clippers snap 3-game losing streak with 130-110 victory over Jazz
